The Senate joint committees on Defense and Army headed by Senator Aliyu Wamakko and Senator Ali Ndume respectively have screened the newly appointed Chief Of Army Staff, Major-General Farouk Yahaya behind closed doors.  President Muhammadu Buhari had announced his appointment a week after the death of Major General Ibrahim Attahiru who died in a plane crash.  Prior to the executive session, the Chief of Army Staff designate who appreciated President Buhari for the appointment promised to tackle insecurity in the country. Speaking with journalists shortly after the screening exercise, Major General Farouk Yahaya promised to provide the right leadership to ensure that the enemies of Nigeria are defeated and thanked the Senate for its cooperation. The Senate panel is expected to produce and submit a report to the chamber containing recommendations as to whether or not the nominee should be confirmed.